summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Pasadena Place, from East Forty-fifth Street to East Fortieth Street, by constructing concrete sidewalks, with all necessary surface drainage, in accordance with Resolution No. 1663 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
